name: HIS 10B
title: United States History, 1877 to 1977
description: Surveys the political, social, and cultural history of the United States from 1877 to 1977. Focuses on national politics with emphasis on how class, race, ethnicity, and gender changed the nation's agenda.NOTE: This course satisfies the American History and Institutions requirement.
class_notes: Enroll in lecture and associated discussion section
